ational contexts in which several languages are taught either as subjects or languages of instruction. Jasone Cenoz proposes the 'Continua of Multilingual Education' as a tool to identify different types of multilingual schools and focuses on Basque educational research to discuss issues that are relevant for other contexts. 'Towards Multilingual Education: Basque Educational Research in International Perspective' is an up to date and comprehensive review of research involving Basque, Spanish and English in Basque schools. The book will be of great value to researchers, professionals and students interested in multilingualism and multilingual education all over the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aBasque language -- Study and teaching -- Spain -- País Vasco. 0aBasque languagexStudy and teachingzSpainzPaís Vasco. 0aEducation, Bilingual -- Spain -- País Vasco. 0aEducation, BilingualzSpainzPaís Vasco. 0aEnglish language -- Study and teaching -- Spain -- País Vasco. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingzSpainzPaís Vasco. 0aLanguage and education -- Spain -- País Vasco. 0aLanguage and educationzSpainzPaís Vasco. 0aMulticultural education -- Spain -- País Vasco. 0aMulticultural educationzSpainzPaís Vasco. 0aMultilingualism -- Spain -- País Vasco. 0aMultilingualismzSpainzPaís Vasco. 0aSecond language acquisitionxStudy and teachingzSpainzPaís Vasco. 0aSpanish language -- Study and teaching -- Spain -- País Vasco. 0aSpanish languagexStudy and teachingzSpainzPaís Vasco. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340